o-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eai1665702600334.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eai1665702600334.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eai1665702600334.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eai1665702600334\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $occmod\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"eai1665702600334___occmod_278520\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the modification status of an occurrence.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"eai1665702600334__topic_d87137e1_d87138e1_d87139e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__p_d87140e1_d87141e1_d87142e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code> }</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__section_w420ab1b7b5_w421ab1b7_w422ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__p_d87143e1_d87144e1_d87145e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">vMod = $occmod (CUSTOMER)</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eai1665702600334__topic_d58002e1_d58003e1_d58004e1_d58005e1_d58006e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832248e84\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__d6157e20__entry__3\">\n Entity name. If omitted, the current entity is used.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eai1665702600334__topic_d58007e1_d58008e1_d58009e1_d58010e1_d58011e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832248e138\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__1\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__2\">\n Occurrence has been removed, or at least one field has been modified. The field can be any database field or a non-database field (if <var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var> is a non-database entity).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__1\">\n 0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__2\">\n Occurrence has not been removed and no field has been modified.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__1\">\n \" \"\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"eai1665702600334__table_d9293e1_d9294e1_d9295e1__entry__2\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var> does not exist or is not included in the component structure.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eai1665702600334__topic_d58012e1_d58013e1_d58014e1_d58015e1_d58016e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832248e209\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__d6417e20\">Allowed in all component types, except self-contained Reports.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eai1665702600334__topic_d58017e1_d58018e1_d58019e1_d58020e1_d58021e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832248e218\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__p_d87161e1_d87162e1_d87163e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> is an occurrence-level function that tests the modification status of data in the current occurrence of the specified entity.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__p_d87164e1_d87165e1_d87166e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> function is set to 0 by the following events:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35057e1_d35058e1_d35059e1\">Each time a component is restarted (unless <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component Behavior</span> is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Keep component definition and data in memory</code>).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35060e1_d35061e1_d35062e1\">By the following ProcScript commands:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35063e1_d35064e1_d35065e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve</span> (Note that <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> can be set to 1 before a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve</span> has been performed.)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35066e1_d35067e1_d35068e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35069e1_d35070e1_d35071e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">release</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35072e1_d35073e1_d35074e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">clear</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35075e1_d35076e1_d35077e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reload</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eai1665702600334__p_d87167e1_d87168e1_d87169e1\">Events that cause a field to be modified (and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> set to 1) include:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35078e1_d35079e1_d35080e1\">The user enters a retrieve profile in an empty field.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35081e1_d35082e1_d35083e1\">The user changes the value of data that has been retrieved.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eai1665702600334__li_d35084e1_d35085e1_d35086e1\">A non-database field is assigned a new value in ProcScript without the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/init</span> switch.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eai1665702600334__section_h1w_q5f_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832248e312\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span></h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">In this example, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> checks whether the current\n               occurrence of CUSTOMER has been modified, and records this status in the message\n               frame.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eai1665702600334__pre_zhm_r5f_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n numeric vMod\nendvariables\nvMod = $occmod (CUSTOMER)\nselectcase vMod \n case 0\n putmess \"The occurrence is unmodified\"\n case 1\n putmess \"The occurrence has been modified\"\nendselectcase\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uni1718715029734.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$formmod (deprecated)</a><p>Return the modification status of data in the current Form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hnz1719661363571.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occcheck</a><p>Return or set the requirement for checking an occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uli1665702604314.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occdbmod</a><p>Return the modification status of a database occurrence.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527052\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527052\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$occmod Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $occmod Return the modification status of an occurrence. $occmod { ( Entity ) } Example: vMod = $occmod (CUSTOMER) Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description Entity String Entity name. If omitted, the current entity is used. Return Values Table 2. Values returned by $occmod Value Meaning 1 Occurrence has been removed, or at least one field has been modified. The field can be any database field or a non-database field (if Entity is a non-database entity). 0 Occurrence has not been removed and no field has been modified. \" \" Entity does not exist or is not included in the component structure. Use Allowed in all component types, except self-contained Reports. Description $occmod is an occurrence-level function that tests the modification status of data in the current occurrence of the specified entity. The $occmod function is set to 0 by the following events: Each time a component is restarted (unless Component Behavior is set to Keep component definition and data in memory ). By the following ProcScript commands: retrieve (Note that $occmod can be set to 1 before a retrieve has been performed.) store release clear reload Events that cause a field to be modified (and $occmod set to 1) include: The user enters a retrieve profile in an empty field. The user changes the value of data that has been retrieved. A non-database field is assigned a new value in ProcScript without the /init switch. Example: Using $occmod In this example, $occmod checks whether the current occurrence of CUSTOMER has been modified, and records this status in the message frame. variables numeric vMod endvariables vMod = $occmod (CUSTOMER) selectcase vMod case 0 putmess \"The occurrence is unmodified\" case 1 putmess \"The occurrence has been modified\" endselectcase Copy Related Links $formmod (deprecated) Return the modification status of data in the current Form component. $occcheck Return or set the requirement for checking an occurrence. $occdbmod Return the modification status of a database occurrence. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}